{"title": "reactive_viz_demo", "hide_code_cells": false, "display_mode": "last", "show_logo": true, "run_on_submit": true, "cells": {"0": {"key": 0, "type": "markdown", "code": "# Interactive Function Visualization\nThis notebook shows how to create dynamic visualizations that react to user input. We'll visualize the superposition of sine waves with adjustable parameters.", "auto_rerun": true, "fragment": false}, "1": {"key": 1, "type": "code", "code": "import numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\n# Create base x values\nx = np.linspace(0, 2*np.pi, 1000)", "auto_rerun": false, "fragment": false}, "2": {"key": 2, "type": "code", "code": "# Interactive controls\namp1 = st.slider('Amplitude 1', 0.0, 2.0, 1.0, key='amp1')\nfreq1 = st.slider('Frequency 1', 1, 5, 1, key='freq1')\nphase1 = st.slider('Phase 1', 0.0, 2*np.pi, 0.0, key='phase1')\n\namp2 = st.slider('Amplitude 2', 0.0, 2.0, 1.0, key='amp2')\nfreq2 = st.slider('Frequency 2', 1, 5, 2, key='freq2')\nphase2 = st.slider('Phase 2', 0.0, 2*np.pi, 0.0, key='phase2')", "auto_rerun": true, "fragment": false}, "3": {"key": 3, "type": "markdown", "code": "### Current wave equation:\n$$y(x) = <<amp1>>\\sin(<<freq1>>x + <<phase1>>) + <<amp2>>\\sin(<<freq2>>x + <<phase2>>)$$", "auto_rerun": true, "fragment": false}, "4": {"key": 4, "type": "code", "code": "# Calculate waves\nwave1 = amp1 * np.sin(freq1 * x + phase1)\nwave2 = amp2 * np.sin(freq2 * x + phase2)\ncombined = wave1 + wave2\n\n# Plot\nplt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\nplt.plot(x, wave1, '--', label='Wave 1')\nplt.plot(x, wave2, '--', label='Wave 2')\nplt.plot(x, combined, '-', label='Combined')\nplt.grid(True)\nplt.legend()\nplt.title('Wave Superposition')\nst.pyplot(plt.gcf())", "auto_rerun": true, "fragment": false}}}